FBIS4-14795 "drsov064_s_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-064 Daily Report 3 Apr 1994 Georgia Abkhazia To Sign Settlement Accords in Moscow Abkhazia To Sign Settlement Accords in Moscow LD0304224594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 2021 GMT 3 Apr 94 LD0304224594 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] Vladislav Ardzinba, leader of the Georgia's separatist region of Abkhazia, has authorized his prime minister Sokrat Dzhindzholia to sign with Georgian officials two agreements in Moscow to settle the Georgian-Abkhazian conflict. Beslan Bargandzhia, spokesman for Abkhazia's legislature, told Interfax one of the accords would enable all ethnic Georgians who have fled Abkhazia and who have taken no part in hostilities against it to return there. The other document is a declaration on the nonviolent settlement of the conflict. The documents, to be signed on Monday, were drafted at Georgian-Abkhazian talks in Geneva, Bargandzhia said.
